Pantheon-ready doctrine

Möbius Zero Doctrine

Zero is not a bottom. It is an anchor on a folded continuity.
The most powerful interventions occur near the twist where orientation is undecided.
At that seam, small, simple, well-timed inputs can bias the next resolved direction more effectively than large force applied after commitment.

Operators

* Seam Sense: detect when a system is near inflection
* Noise Drop: remove excess motion to perceive the hinge
* Hinge Find: identify the variable controlling the flip
* Simple Nudge: apply minimal directional bias
* Release Window: allow self-resolution
* Resolution Read: measure whether the direction took
* Light Reinforcement: support only after genuine propagation

Warning

Past the seam, force gets expensive.
Before the seam, force gets wasted.
At the seam, force should be minimal and precise.

